.TH "ext2_blks_to_allocate" 9 "ext2_blks_to_allocate" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ext2_blks_to_allocate \- Look up the block map and count the number of direct blocks need to be allocated for the given branch.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ext2_blks_to_allocate
.BI "(Indirect * branch "  ","
.BI "int k "  ","
.BI "unsigned long blks "  ","
.BI "int blocks_to_boundary "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "branch" 12
chain of indirect blocks
.IP "k" 12
number of blocks need for indirect blocks
.IP "blks" 12
number of data blocks to be mapped.
.IP "blocks_to_boundary" 12
the offset in the indirect block

return the number of direct blocks to allocate.
